            <thetext>With the upcoming new spec called pointer events [1], our environment check named &quot;event.pointer&quot; is misleading. This check does not check for the availability of the described new pointer events, instead it checks, if the availability of the css key named &quot;pointer-events&quot;.

I think a good idea is to move the key to the css &quot;namespace&quot; and name it css.pointerevents

[1] http://www.w3.org/Submission/pointer-events/
[2] https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/pointer-events</thetext>
